The Continuation to the year 1295 is from a manuscript belonging to Corpus Christi Collega, Cambridge. This continuation, from its com- mencement to the year 1152, consists of a mere transcript from the chronicle of Henry of Hun- tingdon and his continuator. This portion it has been deemed unnecessary to reprint. What follows is a transcript, by the same hand, of the chronicle os John de Taxster, a monk of Bury St. Edmund’s, as sar as the year 1265 inclusive, when the manuscripts of that chronicler termi- nate.
